definitions.definition: To live in a tent or similar temporary accommodation.
examples: We're planning to camp in the field until Sunday.

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To afford rest or lodging for.
( intransitive , sports , video games ) To stay in an advantageous location.
examples: Some players like to camp next to a power-up 's spawning point.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , video games ) To stay beside (something) to gain an advantage.
examples: The easiest way to win on this map is to camp the double damage.
Go and camp the flag for the win .

definitions.definition: ( transitive , video games ) Ellipsis of corpse camp .
( intransitive , obsolete ) To fight ; contend in battle or in any kind of contest; to strive with others in doing anything; compete .
